    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a museum-quality 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2), finished in a flawless Arctic Silver Metallic. This wide-body specimen is powered by a mid-mounted 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, mated to a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is paramount; the IMS bearing has been proactively retrofitted with a ceramic dual-row solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) is bone dry. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec with no bushing fatigue, and the four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers retain their original finish. The undercarriage is free of oxidation, and the bore-scoping report confirms zero cylinder scoring. This is a turn-key, investment-grade 911 for the technical purist.",
